    Test the level of projection done at the level of the scan as a whole; before knowledge of table "implicit" columns or the specific table schema.

      • testBasics

        public void testBasics()
        Basic test: select a set of columns (a, b, c) when the data source has an early schema of (a, c, d). (a, c) are projected, (d) is null.

      • testMap

        public void testMap()
        Map projection occurs when a query contains project-list items with a dot, such as "a.b". We may not know the type of "b", but have just learned that "a" must be a map.

      • testArray

        public void testArray()
        Similar to maps, if the project list contains "a[1]" then we've learned that a is an array, but we don't know what type.

      • testWildcardAndColumns

        public void testWildcardAndColumns()
        Can include both a wildcard and a column name. The Project operator will fill in the column, the scan framework just ignores the extra column.

      • testColumnAndWildcard

        public void testColumnAndWildcard()
        Test a column name and a wildcard.

      • testErrorTwoWildcards

        public void testErrorTwoWildcards()
        Can't include a wildcard twice.

        Note: Drill actually allows this, but the work should be done in the project operator; scan should see at most one wildcard.
